TRIGGERS:
  Special SP that automaticaly run in response to specific event that happen to table.
  Event:
    INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE

TRIGGER TYPES:
DML: (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE)----------------->> AFTER, INSTEAD OF
DDL: CREATE, ALTER, DROP
LOGGON:

SYNTAX:  CREATE TRIGGER TriggerName ON TableName
  WHEN--> (AFTER or INSTEAD OF) INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE    
          BEGIN
   WHAT-->   ---SQL Staement
          END  
